This weekend was pretty cool, went to the bama game with grant and battito. uhh, then i had band practice but i had to record some other bands for vestapalooza.(By the way, be cool kids and come to vestapalooza, everyone will like you more if you do, and my band will kick your ass with our awesome music.) So there was a game tonight, but we lost and that sucked. But the bus ride home was cool so that kinda made up for it, Melissa and Jenny and gayrnt are pretty sorta cool i guess maybe. uhhhhhh, yeah.  so i havent updated in a while and so, loyal readers of my journal, here is what youve been waiting for for a long, long time...............a picture of grant pushing his evil, members-only jacket toting twin, off of a large, badly drawn cliff.

 yessssssssss

This weekend was pretty ok. Went to the rave last night with battito, grant and ryan, and we were gonna see 40 year old virgin, but we got there and it was R, so we tried to sneak in but there were cops everywhere and they told us to go back, so we saw dukes of hazzard and it didnt suck as much as i thought it would. Then we walked around and met these two girls from homewood, they were pretty cool. A lot cooler than most of the other people there.  Then we spent the night at battitos, and that was awesome.
But then i didnt check in with my parents who are out of town and so now im pretty  sure im grounded. So fuck for that, its gay.

Update on recording for anyone who cares, we have seven songs recorded, so that means were about halfway done with the cd and also were the best band ever dammit.
Im back from leadership camp, whooptie doo.

Yep, got some more recording done, and my summer is almost over.

I was told a week ago that on sunday im leaving for leadership training camp, which is by far the gayest thing ive ever heard of. And then in like two weeks im going to Glacier, Montana to go get ate by a bear, which is actually going to be fun, and ill try not to get ate. But then band camp starts the day i get back and then what, we have like a week and a half of summer left. SHIT.

Drum camp is over, hooorraaayyy.

I'm tired, and tomorrow i get to see people that arent in drumline, like my band, and cara.
So that means recording will resume and well have some more songs done.
yep.

Drum camp suuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuckkkkkks


and is ridiculously hard.

yep, went to city stages last night, saw citizen cope which is like laid back R&B stuff, their drummer was pretty good too. And they had two keyboard players, which i thought was cool. After them we ran into the all of the foys minus the parents. Then i saw some local band, and North Mississippi all stars, which was ok, not great, but they did do the coolest thing i saw all night. The drummer got up from the drumset, picked up a washboard and used like wah, chorus and flange effects on it and then the bassisst and the singer(who was on drums now) played like techno beats behind him. that was pretty sweet. And then i saw Govt mule, which was a bit dissapointing, it just didnt work somehow and there was so much bass it felt like some weak dude was throwin steaks at your chest and the bass washed out everything else, it was pretty bad. And then we saw the black crowes, and they were pretty good, i was surprised. Then after them we went to the arbys in the middle of the ghetto with the foys. good times man.

Yeah, so i got all this fancy shmancy digital recording stuff for my birfday. Its pretty kickin. Anyways, this means that my band will probably have a cd ready in a month, possibly sooner, So anyone who asks will get one, maybe not for free, if everyone wants one i might have to put a price on it, you know, supply and demand. but yeah, i havent been doin much lately, except recording and stuff. so, im out.
